  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/841",
  "title": "numericSelector and numericRefinementList APIS",
  "body": "We have different APIS with similar numeric refinements:\n\nnumericSelector:\n\n``` js\nsearch.addWidget(\n  instantsearch.widgets.numericSelector({\n    container: '#popularity-selector',\n    attributeName: 'popularity',\n    operator: '>=',\n    options: [\n      {label: 'Top 10', value: 9900},\n      {label: 'Top 100', value: 9800},\n      {label: 'Top 500', value: 9700}\n    ]\n  })\n);\n```\n\nnumericRefinementList:\n\n``` js\nsearch.addWidget(\n  instantsearch.widgets.numericRefinementList({\n    container: '#popularity',\n    attributeName: 'popularity',\n    options: [\n      {name: 'All'},\n      {end: 4, name: 'less than 4'},\n      {start: 4, end: 4, name: '4'},\n      {start: 5, end: 10, name: 'between 5 and 10'},\n      {start: 10, name: 'more than 10'}\n    ],\n    templates: {\n      header: 'Price'\n    }\n  })\n);\n```\n\nIssues:\n- numericSelector allows all helper operators but you can't do \"BETWEEN\"\n- numericRefinementList allows BETWEEN but you don't know if `end` and `start` are inclusive or exclusive.\n\nCorrect me if I am wrong.\n\nCan we make this more consistent?\n",
